messages.message: @Paul H on crafting (which deployed last evening) I'm seeing it trying to get a bundle by this name: https://crafting-aihub--jessica-instabase.instabase.site.sandboxes.run/static/output/ibapp_aihub.%3C!DOCTYPE%20html%3E%3Chtml%20lang=
Is this because something hasn't deployed yet? It looks like crafting-aihub was deployed successfully at 6pm PT yesterday, which was after you merged your change
Ah, I think you’ll need to rebase on master so that `webpack` will build the new files. Since the backend is now assuming those files exist in webpack.

If you’re seeing a white screen now and you’re on the `ibdev` or `frontend` template, make sure you’re rebased on the latest master! The bundle changes have been deployed to the Crafting cluster, which assumes your webpack is now building the new bundles.
